      "description": "Abaporu (2010), by Alexandre Mury, is a post-conceptual artwork articulated through performance, photography, self-representation, material manifestation, digital image and structured metadata. Created as a performative self-portrait in dialogue with Abaporu (1928), by Tarsila do Amaral, the work critically reactivates the Brazilian modernist canon through imagetic disappropriation and cultural autophagy, while its later inscription in the A.M.O. framework activates the artwork as metadata.",
      "dateCreated": "2010-03-22T16:50:40-03:00",
