      "encodingFormat": "image/jpeg",
      "width": "1000 px",
      "height": "1000 px",
      "dateCreated": "2010-03-22T16:50:40-03:00",
      "caption": "Performative photograph entitled Abaporu (2010), by Alexandre Mury. Performative self-portrait in an open landscape.",
      "description": "Primary digital image associated with Abaporu (2010), a performative self-portrait by Alexandre Mury. The artist appears seated in profile on reddish earth in an open landscape, with the sun positioned between the figure's head and a cactus in backlight, producing a star-shaped luminous effect. The image establishes an intertextual dialogue with Abaporu (1928), by Tarsila do Amaral, while operating through imagetic disappropriation and cultural autophagy.",
      "creator": {
        "@id": "https://id.alexandremury.art/person/alexandre-mury/"
      },
